CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 14, 1962, pg. A14 reads: "At Chi Supper Dance - A partial view of the merrymakers attending the Chi Delta Mu supper dance, last Saturday at the Hilton, can be seen in the above left photo. Guests at the table of the chairman and his wife, Dr. and Mrs. C.C. Bookert, can be seen in the foreground.  Left to right: Mr. and Mrs. George Pitts, Dr. and Mrs. Stanley Pollock, Mrs. Morton Aaronson and Dr. Aaronson, Mrs. Bookert, Mrs. William G. Nunn Jr., Mr. Nunn, Dr. Bookert, Mrs. Jack Moore, Mr. Moore, Mrs. B.J. Weisband, Dr. Weisband, Mr. and Mrs. Alvin Bussey."
TitMainTitle: Group seated around table from left: George Pitts, Phyllis Pitts, Dr. and Mrs. Stanley Pollock, Dr. and Mrs. Morton Aaronson, Mabel Bookert, Frances Bell Nunn, unknown, William G. Nunn Jr., Dr. C. C Bookert, Jane Moore, Jack Moore, Dr. and Mrs. B. J. Weisband, Alvin Bussey, and Elva Bussey, in Hilton Hotel for Chi Delta Mu supper dance
